# 12. Challenges Encountered During Development

Several challenges were encountered during development of the project.

## 12.1 Thread Synchronization Problems

During multithreading implementation, inconsistent results occurred because multiple threads accessed shared variables simultaneously.

This caused:

* Incorrect counter values
* Data inconsistency
* Unpredictable execution

### Solution

Mutexes and semaphores were implemented to synchronize thread access.

This solved the race condition problem.

## 12.2 Process Coordination

Managing parent-child process relationships required careful tracking of process states.

### Solution

Parent PID fields and PCB structures were used to maintain process hierarchy.

## 12.3 Integration Between C and Python

Integrating low-level C components with Python scheduling modules required proper execution coordination.

### Solution

A Python controller was implemented to launch and coordinate scheduling operations.

## 12.4 Data Persistence

Tracking process state changes over time required a storage mechanism.

### Solution

JSON serialization was implemented using PCB snapshot files.


